SIMPLE: hindrance
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hindrance
<hw>Hin"drance</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Hinder</er>, <pos>v. t.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of
hindering, or the state of being hindered.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which hinders; an impediment.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>What various <qex>hindrances</qex> we meet.</q>
<rj><qau>Cowper.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Something between a <qex>hindrance</qex> and a help.</q>
<rj><qau>Wordsworth.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Impediment; obstruction; obstacle; difficulty;
interruption; check; delay; restraint.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>hindshank</ent>⟦br⟧
